data.description: WELCOME HOME to this vacant and move-in ready beauty. The WHOLE interior was just freshly painted and ready for the next owners! $2500 seller credit with acceptable offer! Located in DD2 School District and minutes from Historic Summerville, the home is convenient to multiple roadways that will get you around town FAST! The neighborhood is within waking distance to a shopping center with Publix grocery, several restaurants and stores. As you enter the neighborhood, you will be greeted by roads lined with Oak trees, green spaces galore, RV/Boat storage on site, and sidewalks/walking trails that span the entire area. When you pull up to the house, you will immediately notice the freshly painted exterior (2022) and perfectly manicured lawn with irrigatioEntering the home, you'll enjoy how open and bright the home is with the fresh paint. One of very few homes in the neighborhood that has a Master Bedroom on the ground floor which includes a walk-in closet, garden tub and separate shower, this home has been used by a multi-generational family in several ways. Perfect for family gatherings, the downstairs has an open kitchen and dining area that moves into the family room with tall ceilings and a gas fireplace. Upstairs you have 3 additional HUGE bedrooms, full bath and a bonus storage space that doesn't require you to climb attic stairs! This home has been well taken care of with a new roof (2023), exterior paint (2022) interior paint(last week), new window screens(2023), new water heater(2022) and so much more that will save you THOUSANDS...check them off your "to do" list!  Outside, the yard is perfect and low maintenance. You have a quaint space to enjoy grilling out, area for the dog or kids, a detached 2 car garage and additional parking for 2-3 more cars that is all accessed by a private alleyway. White Gables has a ton of amenities that include a pool, kids pool, playground, clubhouse that hosts a variety of events for homeowners, tennis courts, athletic fields, pickleball court, basketball court and tons of greenspaces and walkways for all to enjoy! Ask about how to get a $2000 credit for closing costs by using preferred lender!
